    "CUI: concept unique identifier. 2 (2MedCAT).",
    "These Python tools, both open source and publicly available, were initially designed for extracting concepts from English texts and have been adapted for Dutch[6,21].",
    "1 https://github.com/medspacy/medspacy MedSpaCy extends the spaCy software library for clinical NLP tasks, including clinical concept extraction, using an adaptation of QuickUMLS-a tool for fast, unsupervised biomedical concept extraction based on string similarity and a reference concept dictionary.",
    "For English concept extraction, we utilized all UMLS concepts with English terms.",
    "For Dutch concept extraction, we used all Dutch vocabularies from UMLS and replaced the English Systematized Nomenclature of Medicine Clinical Terms (SNOMED CT) vocabulary with the Dutch SNOMED CT translation 3, maintained by NICTIZ, the Dutch National IT Institute for Healthcare 44 Figure 2.2Figure 2."
